'''Andrea Feltrini''', called also '''Andrea di Cosimo''', was a [[Florence|Florentine]] painter who excelled in [[grotesque]]s. He was born on 12 March 1477, and died on 12 May 1548.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Thiem|first1=Christel|title=Dizionario Biografico degli Italiani - Volume 46|date=1996|publisher=Treccani|url=http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/andrea-feltrini_%28Dizionario-Biografico%29/}}</ref> His works are to be met with at Florence on the fronts of houses, on walls, and on ceilings. He is called by the first name, from his having been a scholar of [[Morto da Feltre]], and by the second from his having studied art under [[Cosimo Rosselli|Cosimo Roselli]].

