'''Brian Keeble''' is a British author and editor.<ref>''Religion: Beyond a Concept'' (2007) Hent De Vries p. 981. "In contrast to, e.g., Pierre Boulez, who is a prolific writer himself, Tavener has used a ghost writer for his most important book to date, Brian Keeble, ed., John Tavener: The Music of Silence".</ref> He is the founder of Golgonooza Press and a co-founder of the ''Temenos'' and [[Temenos Academy]].<ref>[http://www.temenosacademy.org/temenos_journal.html Temenos Academy Review]</ref>
==Biography== Keeble is the founder of Golgonooza Press where he worked as editor, designer and publisher from 1974-2004.<ref>Keeble, Brian. ''Every man an artist''. [[World Wisdom|World Wisdom Books]], 2005. 245. Print.</ref>
He was a co-founder and is a Fellow of the [[Temenos Academy]] - whose Patron is [[HRH The Prince of Wales|Charles, Prince of Wales]] - which is a teaching organization dedicated to the same central idea that had inspired the earlier ''Temenos'', of which he was a co-founder and editor (1980–1991).<ref>[http://www.worldwisdom.com/public/authors/Brian-Keeble.aspx Author Page] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100222022329/http://www.worldwisdom.com/public/authors/Brian-Keeble.aspx |date=February 22, 2010 }}</ref> Both focus on a devotion to the ‘Arts of the Imagination’ and feature the lectures and works of scholars and teachers committed to [[Perennial Philosophy]].
The Golgonooza Press Archive, covering the years 1962 to 2012, is in the British Library Department of Manuscripts (Add MS 89131).
